“测温枪”到底是怎样测出你的温度的？。
How did the Thermostat measure your temperature?
地球人研究报告。
Earthman Study Report.
文化。
Culture.
当下这些天，大街上最威风的就是公共场所的安保人员和各小区的工作人员了。
These days, the street is the most majestic security personnel in public places and community workers.
不管你平时多大派头，也不管你哪个星球来的，遇见他们咱都得乖乖过去，要么举起手来、要么头伸过去，挨上一枪。
No matter how pompous you are, or whatever planet you come from, we'll have to come along and either raise our hands or stick our heads out and get shot.
。
.
测温现场1。
Temperature scene 1.
测温现场2（图中是测温枪，谢谢）。
Temperature scene 2 (pictured here is a temperature gun, thank you).
虽然这几天大家挨的枪子不少被检测的次数不少，但对很多朋友来说，这玩意在之前的生活中还相对比较少见。
Although people have been shot several times in the past few days, but for many friends, this gadget is relatively rare in previous life.
因为对它的陌生，进而就衍生出了一个个萦绕在脑边问题。
Because of its strange, and then derived from a haunting in the brain.
。
.
测温枪是为何在你脑袋上“打一枪”就知道温度的；它测得到底准不准；以及亲戚群里最关心的，被这玩意打多了会不会影响健康？。
Why does a thermometer know the temperature by "hitting a bullet" on your head? Is it accurate? And what do relatives care most about being hit too much by it?
这些问题，其实只要搞懂测温枪的原理，就会一一迎刃而解。
These problems, in fact, as long as understand the principle of temperature gun, will be solved one by one.
原理虽然复杂，但不用担心，看了小姨的讲解，保准咱二舅姥爷瞅了都能理解得明明白白儿的。
Although the principle is complex, but do not worry, read the aunt's explanation, to ensure that my uncle and grandmother can understand clearly.
。
.
被测温枪打多了会不会有损健康。
Is it bad for your health to be hit too much with a thermostat?
被测温枪打多了会不会有损健康？——这个问题很经典。
Is it bad for your health to be hit too much with a thermostat? It's a classic question.
。
.
测温枪，学名是“红外线测温仪”或者“红外线辐射测温仪”。
Thermostats, known as infrared thermometers or infrared radiation thermometers.
很多人一听到“红外”“辐射”这类的词就一哆嗦，直接吓尿。
Many people shiver when they hear such words as "infrared" or "radiation," directly scaring the urine.
。
.
说起来，历来包含“红外”“辐射”的设备科普起来总是一件麻烦事。
To put it in perspective, devices that have traditionally contained "infrared" and "radiation" are always a nuisance.
要知道在“亲戚群”里，才没有人信你说的“任何物体都辐射”；更不会有人跟你谈什么剂量。
You know, in the Relatives group, no one believes what you mean by "anything radiates"; not to mention what dose you get.
他们只知道只要“有辐射”，就应该“宁可信其有”。
They only know that as long as there is "radiation," it should be "trusted."
。
.
遗憾的是，测温枪这玩意虽然名头上冠着“辐射”和“红外”，但不会对你的身体施加任何哪怕一丁点的影响。
Unfortunately, the thermostat, though branded with "radiation" and "infrared," does not affect your body at all.
。
.
因为它是个接收器，不是发射器。
Because it's a receiver, not a transmitter.
。
.
笼统的说，红外测温仪的原理是：被动吸收目标的红外辐射能量，从而获得物体温度数值。
In general, the infrared thermometer principle is: passive absorption of the target's infrared radiation energy, so that the temperature value of the object.
。
.
意思就是，你的身体无时无刻在向外扩散辐射能量，而测温枪的作用，是接收你身体某区域的辐射能量。
This means that your body radiates radiant energy out all the time, and the thermostat serves to receive the radiation energy from an area of your body.
如果真的说这个过程有什么危害的话，那么应该担心被辐射的也是测温枪，没准万一哪天测到个1000℃的脑门自己就憋了。
If there is any harm to the process, then it is the temperature gun that should be irradiated, perhaps in the event that one day a 1,000 degrees Celsius forehead is detected.
。
.
所以这玩意虽然长着一副枪的样子，但只有被动挨打的份。
So even though this thing has the appearance of a gun, it's only a passive part of it.
。
.
好了，说明白这个问题，也许有些小伙伴就想抢答了——是不是这就意味着，测温枪的工作过程就是像温度计一样，直接隔空感受你散发的“温度信号”呢？——这样的说法其实也不太对。
Well, to get the point across, some of your friends might want to snap a response - does that mean that a thermostat works like a thermometer, directly isolating your "temperature signal"?
。
.
红外测温枪能接收到的，只是各种波段的电磁波，绝不是直接的温度传导。
Infrared temperature measurement gun can receive, only the electromagnetic waves of various bands, is not the direct temperature conduction.
而其中最关键的，从“电磁波信息”到“温度信息”的这一转换过程，就要提到今天要说的真正的重点了——黑体辐射定律。
The most important of these, from "electromagnetic wave information" to "temperature information" this conversion process, will be referred to today's real focus - the law of black body radiation.
。
.
黑体辐射定律。
The Law of Blackbody Radiation.
当你试图在中文媒体平台上搜索任何科技产品的原理时，除了会找到一些假装科普的复制粘贴怪，就是一些读理论、贴公式的读课本式的天书。
When you try to search for the principles of any tech product on a Chinese media platform, you'll find only a few copy-and-paste monsters pretending to copy and paste the science - books that read theories and paste formulas.
。
.
小姨喜欢把这种不负责任的科普称为“懒科普”。
Auntie likes to call this irresponsible science "lazy science."
具体到这次的“测温枪原理”就是——他们几乎只会煞有介事地搬出基于黑体辐射定律的那段话：。
In this particular case, the "temperature gun principle" is - they will almost certainly respectfully quote the passage based on the law of black-body radiation:
自然界中一切高于绝对零度（-273.15℃）的物体都在不停向外辐射能量，物体的向外辐射能量的大小及其按波长的分布与它的表面温度有着十分密切的联系，物体的温度越高，所发出的红外辐射能力越强。
Everything in nature above absolute zero (-273.15 ° C) radiates energy outward, and the magnitude of the object's outward radiation energy and its distribution by wavelength are very closely related to its surface temperature, and the higher the temperature of the object, the stronger its infrared radiation capability.
。
.
诚然，这句话是一切的基础，但是我相信如果不对里面的句子进行拆解，不解释黑体辐射的理论，几乎没有人能沉下心来去理解这话到底说了个什么意思。
It is true that this is the basis of everything, but I am convinced that few people will be able to grasp the meaning of this statement without dismantling the sentences and explaining the theory of black-body radiation.
。
.
哎，这事其实很简单。
Well, it's actually very simple.
。
.
这个黑体辐射定律是干啥用的呢，说白了就是物理学家想搞懂“电磁波信息”到“温度（能量）信息”的转换关系。
What does this black-body radiation law do? To put it bluntly, physicists want to understand the relationship between "electromagnetic wave information" and "temperature (energy) information."
。
.
于是他们假想出了“黑体”这个东西。
So they imagined the thing in black.
。
.
这个时候我们继续派出小姨的老朋友 卡比 出场。
At the same time we continued to send out our old friend, Cabby.
假设“黑卡比”就是一个标准的“黑体”，它的特性是：入射的电磁波全部被吸收，既没有反射，也没有透射。
Assuming that the black-card ratio is a standard "black body," it is characterized by the absorption of all incoming electromagnetic waves, neither reflected nor transmitted.
。
.
体现到卡比身上就是，吃掉的食物从来不吐出去，没有浪费地全部自己消化掉。
Carbi is reflected in the body, eat the food never spit out, do not waste all their own digestion.
。
.
那么，消化掉的东西，最后就变成了卡比体内的热量，也就是热辐射（我们可以把它通俗地理解为温度）。
What is digested, then, ends up as the calories in Cabby's body, or heat radiation (colloquially understood as temperature).
于是这个从“电磁辐射”（光）到“热辐射”（热）的过程，就叫黑体辐射。
So this process from "electromagnetic radiation" (light) to "thermal radiation" (heat), known as black body radiation.
。
.
好了，知道了这个原理，现在新的问题来了——我们该怎么知道黑体吸进去的“光”到底转化成了多少“热”呢？。
Well, now that we know the principle, here comes the new question - how do we know how much heat the "light" in black has turned into?
这个问题自从17世纪牛顿发现三棱镜光色散现象的时候就开始研究了，科学家们一直钻研了数百年，终于在1900年的时候，马克思·普朗克在德国物理学会上公布了靠谱的“黑体辐射定律公式”。
The problem has been studied since Newton discovered the prismatic dispersion of light in the 17th century, and scientists have been studying it for hundreds of years. Finally, in 1900, Marx Planck published the spectral "formula of the laws of black-body radiation" at the German Society of Physics.
。
.
黑体辐射定律公式。
Black body radiation law formula.
其中为了证明这一公式而引出的衍生品“量子力学”概念，顺道成为了现代物理学的两大基本支柱之一。
The concept of "quantum mechanics" of derivatives, derived to prove this formula, has become one of the two fundamental pillars of modern physics.
。
.
人类得到这个公式多不容易，看看它是用多少颜值换来的就知道了：。
It's not easy for humans to get this formula, just look at how much it costs.
所以，为了让这消耗掉的颜值不被辜负，我们现在就了解一下这个公式，别看写起来复杂，其实都是纸老虎，它所揭示的无非是光与温度的关系——。
So, in order to live up to the lost face value, we now have a look at this formula, which, although complicated, is nothing more than a paper tiger, which reveals nothing more than the relationship between light and temperature.
你看如果把它画成图，是不是就好懂一些了！（并没有）。
Do you think it would be easier to figure it out? (No) No.
怎么理解这个图呢，这几条线的走势反映的是某个固定温度（单位K/国际标准温度单位）下，不同波长的热辐射强度。
The trend of these lines reflects the intensity of thermal radiation at different wavelengths at a given temperature (in units of K / ISO).
。
.
比如里面的6000K（5727°C），这是太阳的温度——于是根据黑体辐射定律公式，我们就能分别算出太阳光中不同波长（比如红色、绿色、蓝色、某段红外线、某段紫外线……）的热辐射能量（强度/I）是多少。
For example, the 600K (5727 ° C) is the temperature of the sun - so that, according to the formula of the laws of black-body radiation, we can calculate the heat radiation energy (intensity / I) of different wavelengths of sunlight (such as red, green, blue, some infrared, some ultraviolet...).
。
.
同理，如果我们知道某段光的热辐射强度和光线波长，也可以算出其代表的“温度”是多少了。
Similarly, if we know the intensity and wavelength of light, we can calculate the "temperature" that it represents.
。
.
好的，我知道说到这很多同学还是想说“依然看不懂”，没关系，这会儿看睡着的同学可以醒醒了，咱把理解难度继续降维，下面才是重点。
I can't understand it, but I can't understand it. I can't make it up to you. I can't make it up to you.
。
.
我们只要看懂一点，就是——高温度下的黑体辐射强度，在任何一个波长范围内，都高于低温度下的黑体辐射。
All we need to understand is that black-body radiation at high temperatures is higher than black-body radiation at low temperatures in any wavelength range.
。
.
反映到图里就是，1500℃的红色高温曲线，在每段波长上强度都比1200℃的黄色曲线高：。
The picture shows that the red high temperature curve at 1500 ℃ is higher than the yellow curve at 1200 ℃ in every wavelength:
红外测温仪就是根据这一特性设计出来的。
Infrared thermometer is designed according to this characteristic.
。
.
在这个理论基础下，根据工程应用所需的测量精度不同，红外测温仪有三种主要的设计方向。
On the basis of this theory, the infrared thermometer has three main design directions according to the different measurement accuracy needed in the engineering application.
。
.
其一，单色测温法：利用单一波长下的单色辐射强度比值来判断温度；。
First, the monochrome temperature measurement method: the use of a single wavelength ratio of monochrome radiation intensity to judge temperature;
其二，双色测温法：测量被测物体在两个波长下的辐射强度比值的强度变化来判断，这种方法比前者受外界影响更小，误差也更小；。
Second, the two-color temperature measurement method: to measure the measured object in two wavelengths of the intensity of the intensity ratio changes, this method is less affected by the outside world, and less error;
前面这两种能不能理解看个人造化，我们详细说一下第三种——。
Whether the two above can understand to see the individual creation, we say the third in detail - -.
其三，全辐射测温法。
Third, all-radiation temperature measurement.
。
.
全辐射测温法名字听起来最牛逼，但其实是三种方法里精度相对最差的一种，不过优势就在于结构简单，成本较低。
All-radiation thermometry sounds like the best, but it's the least accurate of the three, but it has the advantage of being simple in structure and low in cost.
。
.
原因就在于其“大力出奇迹”式的设计思路——全辐射测温法，是通过测量辐射物体的全波长的热辐射总强度，来确定物体的辐射温度的。
The reason lies in its "vigorously miraculous" design idea - all-radiation temperature measurement, by measuring the total radiation intensity of radiation objects at all wavelengths, to determine the object's radiation temperature.
。
.
我们怎么理解这个概念呢，就是好比把一个温度下的全波段辐射强度图比做一个米山，现在让卡比把整个米山全部吃掉，我们来测它吃掉后转化的热辐射能量总共有多少，最终推导出当时的温度值。
How do we understand this concept, that is, a temperature of the full-band radiation intensity of the image than a mountain, now let Cabby eat the whole of the rice, we eat it into the total heat energy converted, and finally derive the temperature value at that time.
。
.
全辐射测温法过程。
All-radiation temperature measurement process.
现在小区门口给你测体温的红外线测温枪，基本都是这一思路设计的。
Now the cell door to your temperature infrared temperature measurement gun, are basically designed in this way.
。
.
所以思路缕清后，我们只需把一个这样的卡比放在测温枪中，测量出它吸收辐射后释放的热辐射量，就能换算出被测物对应的温度了。
So just put one of these cards in a temperature measuring gun, measure the amount of radiation it absorbs, and calculate the corresponding temperature.
。
.
这个能将接收到的“红外电磁波辐射”转换为“热辐射”（黑体辐射过程），进而把“热辐射”转化为电信号（热电转化过程）的东西就是：热释电红外传感器（简称：PIR）。
This can be received "infrared electromagnetic wave radiation" into "thermal radiation" (blackbody radiation process), then "thermal radiation" into electrical signals (thermoelectric conversion process) things: pyroelectric infrared sensors (PIR).
简单列一下这东西的工作原理：。
Make a simple list of how this works:
顺便说一下，这玩意还真不贵：。
By the way, it's not expensive.
测温枪到底准不准。
Temperature guns are on target.
好了，原理搞明白，又可以回到接地气的问题上了。
Okay, the principle is clear, and we can go back to the grounding problem.
所以另一个大家很关心的问题，就是这玩意测得准不准呢？。
So the other thing we all care about is whether this thing is accurate?
影响测量结果的原因是多方面的。
There are many factors that influence the measurement results.
。
.
其一，客观物理因素：。
First, objective physical factors:
由于“黑体辐射定律”是在工作物质是理论黑体的情况下演算的，而生活中物质因为材质关系都是属于不同“纯度”的黑体，这个纯度用“发射率”来表示。
Since the "law of black body radiation" is calculated in the case of working matter is black-body theory, the material in life because of material relations are different "purity" in bold, this purity is expressed in "emissivity."
。
.
理论黑体的发射率是1，平时我们测温枪用的大多数都是0.95的发射率，这适用于生活中大多数的情况。
The theoretical black body emissivity is 1, at ordinary times we measure the temperature gun most of the emissivity is 0.95, this applies to most situations in life.
所以你可以观察一下，你能见到的测温枪显示屏基本上都会写着“0.95”的字样。
So you can see that the display of a thermostat gun you can see basically says "0. 95."
。
.
但这个0.95毕竟是根据被测物的材质而定的浮动值，这是测温枪很难绝对准确的原因之一。
But this 0.95 is based on the material of the object being tested, which is one of the reasons it is difficult to be absolutely accurate.
。
.
其二，污染因素：。
Second, pollution factors:.
由于信息是通过电磁辐射（光）传导的，这不可避免的会受到烟尘和水蒸气等外界因素的影响；另外，机器入射口处的透镜污染也是干扰项的一环。
Since information is transmitted by electromagnetic radiation (light), this is inevitably influenced by external factors such as soot and water vapour. In addition, lens contamination at the machine's inlet is also part of the interference.
。
.
其三，机器精度：。
Third, machine accuracy:.
因为成本原因，我们平时所用的测温枪大多没有用更精确的双色测温法技术，内部元件的精细度也参差不齐；再有就是使用时的距离误差导致的数值波动了。
For cost reasons, most of the temperature measuring guns we use today do not use more accurate dual-color temperature measurement techniques, the fineness of internal components is uneven, and the range error in use causes numerical fluctuations.
。
.
但是，这些有限的缺点还是很难成为我们拒绝测温枪的理由。
However, these limited shortcomings still make it difficult for us to reject thermostat guns.
。
.
现在我们正在使用的红外测温枪，比传统的热传导测温方式还是优秀太多了——响应时间短、测温效率高，不用接触被测物体依然可以有着相对可靠的准确度，同时制作成本低廉，操作起来也足够方便。
The infrared thermostat we are using is still far superior to the conventional heat transfer method - short response time, high temperature measurement efficiency, relatively reliable accuracy without contact with the object under test, low cost and easy to operate.
。
.
所以反过来想想，有这么多客观因素的影响，红外测温枪依然能保证测量温度维持在相对精确的范围内，这本身就是一种很厉害的事。
So the converse is that, with so many objective factors, the infrared thermostat ensures that the temperature is kept within a relatively accurate range, which is a serious matter in itself.
它没有那么完美，但依然是一种有限范围内，可以选择到的好产品。
It's not that perfect, but it's still a limited range of good products to choose from.
。
.
至少在今天来看，我已经很难想像，这次防疫战中如果没有类似的科技产品的存在，仅仅是测体温这项一项，就会给防控工作带来多大的困难了。
For now, at least, I can't imagine how difficult it would be to control the disease without a similar technology.
。
.
而对小姨来说，这次能借此机会说明白测温枪的原理，能传递出多少知识倒是其次，最在意的，还是能有幸和大家再次从世界的一个角度，见证科学的力量吧。
But for auntie, this time to explain the principle of the temperature gun, how much knowledge can pass on is the second, the most important thing is to have the honor and everyone once again from a world perspective, to witness the power of science.
。
.
